Though love is considered a positive and desirable aspect of existence, love can cause a great deal of emotional harm. Consider [[Romeo and Juliet]], [[Othello]], [[Great Expectations]], and other classical and popular works that enumerate how love can lead to tragedy and emotional pain. In human interactions, love becomes a peril when love is not bilateral, known as [[Unrequited love]]. A futher peril for individuals that love, or can love others, is that love is not enduring and that many people have psychological [[defense mechanisms]] inhibit their ability to accept or reciprocate love.
